 the US President has constructed a dillemma just so that the US is guaranteed war in Iraq.<br>
<br>
Here is the problem:<br>
<br>
1) Iraq must allow for new unconditional weapons inspections per agreement in 1991. If not then the US and her allies will strike militarily even with out support of the UN Security council.<br>
<br>
2) Iraq has agreed to the terms of unconditional weapon inspections as defined in 1991 after the Gult War, but that is no longer good enough. The UN Security council needs to frame a new resolution, which Russia is sure to reject if it involves any unilateral military action by the US and or Britain. In which case, the US will claim that the weapons inspections per the already agreed upon terms lack enforceability and will wage war against Iraq any way.<br>
<br>
In either case, Iraq is sure to get the living snot bombed out of them all because the President is not willing to see any other viable solution to this problem. <p><HTML><IMG SRC="http://64.81.30.48/lurisig.jpg" HSPACE="150" WIDTH="330" HEIGHT="185" BORDER="0"> </HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urheaton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rheaton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/2/02 5:02:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=327.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Latest Recipe for War...</span><hr size=1> &quot;This isn't about weapons inspections..it's about disarmament&quot;<br>
<br>
The U.S. claims it has absolute proof that Iraq has weapons of mass destruction. However, the UN wants to scrap the last 11 years and start the process all over nice and new (back to the beginning - 91 resolutions).<br>
<br>
Obeying the law:<br>
The existing resolutions are law...law that Iraq has broke time and time again. How many &quot;clean slates&quot; are we going to give him? How many times do you tell a child to clean their room before you act and punish them for disobedience?<br>
<br>
I heard it explained like this:<br>
You have a child whom you suspect has Crack in his room. You have a standing rule in your house &quot;No crack in this house, ever!&quot; Yet the child will not let you search their room... locking and barring the doors.<br>
<br>
You impose sanctions.. You ground them, take away allowance, no TV, no phone, etc, but still he will not let you search his room.<br>
<br>
You tell the child &quot;Crack is illegal..we are calling the police and they will take care of it!&quot;  Under fear of the police the child then agrees to let you search only parts of the room. Closet and dresser are off limits though. <br>
<br>
Is this negotiation acceptable?<br>
<br>
I think that most of us are missing the point all together. Saddam wants weapons of mass destruction. ..he will continue to build them... he will continue to employ them when he can. No, we dont assassinate the child cause he likes his Crack, but we do totally remove his ability to obtain and use it. <p><font color=#FFaa36>
<b>Rheaton Stormcast <br>
57th Season Magician <br>
